article.description: Torrion Brummit had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and Mike Brown scored 17 as Western Carolina pulled away in the second half en route to an 88-63 win over Hiwassee Tuesday night.
article.headline: Western Carolina tops Hiwassee 88-63
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Torrion Brummit had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and Mike Brown scored 17 as Western Carolina pulled away in the second half en route to an 88-63 win over Hiwassee Tuesday night. Brummit was 6 of 9 from the field and scored 13 of his 18 points in the second half. Western Carolina (2-2) led 46-38 with 13:34 remaining and used a 17-4 run in the next 3:31 to win its second straight at home to start the season. Twelve different players scored for the Catamounts. Jordan Sexton had 13 points and Kevis Jackson 12 for Hiwassee (4-6). Both players went 5 of 8 from the field. The Catamounts dominated on the glass, grabbing 61 rebounds compared to the Tigers' 36 and leading 29-10 in second-chance points. Western Carolina led by as many as 31 in the second half.
